# Non-code paths kept OUT of the OpenWiki code map (rsync --exclude-from).
# PKIS's code map documents the Python backend + tools + tests only — the wiki/ knowledge
# graph (2,900+ nodes) is CONTENT, not code, and must never be fed to OpenWiki.
wiki/
raw/
docs/
viewer/
.venv/
.git/
openwiki/
__pycache__/
node_modules/
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-*
*.npz
*.log
# Secrets never enter the staging copy OpenWiki reads.
.env
.env.*
# Binary / image / media / font files break OpenWiki (base64 document media_type error).
*.svg
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.ico
*.webp
*.pdf
*.woff
*.woff2
*.ttf
*.eot
*.mp4
*.mov
*.zip
*.gz
*.parquet
# HTML/notebooks: OpenWiki base64-attaches these as documents (media_type != pdf → 400).
*.html
*.htm
*.ipynb
package-lock.json
